definition: to hand in/to hand over/to seize

sentences.english: The accounting office checked off each worker's dues every month.
sentences.chinese: 會計部門每月扣除每個工人的應繳費用。

sentences.english: Life expectancy at retirement is one of key factors related closely with contribution rate of personal account.
sentences.chinese: 平均餘命是影響個人賬戶繳費率的重要因素之一。

sentences.english: Please go to the cashier to pay fees first.
sentences.chinese: 請您先到批價櫃檯繳費。

sentences.english: I assure you this late-payment thing will never happen again.
sentences.chinese: 我向你保證這種延遲繳費的事兒再也不會有了。

sentences.english: NO application dossier can be returned, and the application fee is NOn-refundable.
sentences.chinese: 未錄取者，其申請表件及所繳費用均不退還。
只有繳費的反鋸齒字體。

sentences.english: If the recessive debt is undertaken by the state finance, payment rate drops to 18%.
sentences.chinese: 如果隱性債務由國家財政承擔，繳費率降爲18%。

sentences.english: If the class have not enough student, the class would be cancelled. The school fee can be refund.
sentences.chinese: 若因人數不足無法開班，已繳費用可無息退還。

sentences.english: If you choose to pay once per term, please pay ten days before the term begins.
sentences.chinese: 按學期繳費的家長請在開學前十天交清本學期費用。
我來付電費，這是繳費卡。

sentences.english: Any fees paid are not refundable unless the course is cancelled by the organizers.
sentences.chinese: 除非有關課程被取消，否則已繳費用，概不發還。

sentences.english: It will be very convenient to pay for such expenses as tuition fees with a UnionPay card.
sentences.chinese: 在繳納學費時，用銀聯卡刷卡繳費會比較方便。

sentences.english: Please bring a copy of your dorm deposit receipt to Life Guidance Section.
sentences.chinese: 請攜帶住宿保證金之繳費收據影本至生活輔導組辦理。

sentences.english: if anyone is re-unemployed after reemployment, the time period of paying premiums shall be recalculated.
sentences.chinese: 重新就業後，再次失業的，繳費時間重新計算。

sentences.english: Present staff card together with the parking ticket at Shroff Office or Customer Care Centers.
sentences.chinese: 於停車場繳費處或顧客服務中心出示職員證及泊車卡。

sentences.english: Telephone users are required to pay their bills at the telecommunications office.
sentences.chinese: 請固定電話用戶按時到電信局繳費。

definition: to hand in/to hand over/to seize
to fill in a form/to write data in a box (on a questionnaire or web form)
to pay/to hand over (tax payment etc)
to return (sth borrowed etc)/to send back/to refund/to rebate
to transfer (money to a bank account)
